# Recursive fibonacci with memo via a vec.
*fib(n as i64) returns i64
    if n < 2
        return n
    memo is vec()
    i is 0
    while i <= n
        memo.push(0)
        i is i + 1
    memo.set(0, 0)
    memo.set(1, 1)
    i is 2
    while i <= n
        memo.set(i, memo.get(i - 1) + memo.get(i - 2))
        i is i + 1
    memo.get(n)

*main
    log fib(30)
